name: ALBUM - "The Kinetics of a Decaying Structure"
description: D-Rails album “The Kinetics of A Decaying Structure” Kerrang Review! 4 out of 5 KKKK’s Killer Debut For Leeds Hardcore Mob. Some Bands get right good at playing together because they spend every night in their rehearsal room. D-Rail are the other type. Clocking up an average 100 shows a year, they’ve got that bullet-proof edge that bands get when they’ve perfected their trade in front of an audience, making each song as deadly as they do tight The energetic, angular hardcore rush of opener ‘Lines Drawn’ could get you starting a pit in your living room, as do the 10 tracks that follow, flying out of your speakers with infectious, vital energy, leaving you positively itching to see them in the flesh.
